data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script type="litespeed/javascript">(adsbygoogle=window.adsbygoogle||[]).push({})</script></div><li id="wprm-recipe-22558-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Prepare <a href="https://vegecravings.com/dry-garlic-chutney">dry garlic chutney</a>. You can store this chutney also for 4-5 days.</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image" style="text-align: center;"><img data-lazyloaded="1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4NjQiIGhlaWdodD0iNjAyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODY0IDYwMiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=" decoding="async" width="864" height="602" data-src="https://vegecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dry-garlic-chutney-step-by-step-recipe-1024x714.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Dry Garlic Chutney Recipe" /></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-22558-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Heat oil in a pan and add rai (mustard seeds). When the seeds start to crackle, add curry leaves along with paste of ginger, garlic and green chillies.</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredients wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredients-inline wprm-block-text-faded" style="margin-top: -5px; margin-bottom: 5px;"><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-2" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">7-8 Curry Leaves, </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-4" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">3 Garlic Cloves, </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-5" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1/2 Inch Ginger, </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-6" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1/2 Teaspoon Rai (Black Mustard Seeds), </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-11" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1 Tablespoon Cooking Oil, </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-3" data-separator="" style="margin-bottom: 5px;">2 Green Chillies</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image" style="text-align: center;"><img data-lazyloaded="1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4NjQiIGhlaWdodD0iNzk2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODY0IDc5NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=" decoding="async" width="864" height="796" data-src="https://vegecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/batata-vada-recipe-step-by-step-instructions-1-1024x943.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Batata Vada Recipe Step By Step Instructions 1" /></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-22558-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Add turmeric powder, red chilli powder, heeng (asafoetida) and salt to the pan.</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredients wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredients-inline wprm-block-text-faded" style="margin-top: -5px; margin-bottom: 5px;"><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-7" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1/2 Teaspoon Red Chilli Powder, </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-8" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1/2 Teaspoon Turmeric Powder (Haldi), </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-9" data-separator=", " style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1/4 Teaspoon Heeng (Asafoetida), </span><span class="wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient wprm-recipe-instruction-ingredient-22558-10" data-separator="" style="margin-bottom: 5px;">1 Teaspoon Salt</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image" style="text-align: center;"><img data-lazyloaded="1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4NjQiIGhlaWdodD0iNzI1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODY0IDcyNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=" decoding="async" width="864" height="725" data-src="https://vegecravings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/batata-vada-recipe-step-by-step-instructions-2-1024x859.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large" alt="Batata Vada Recipe Step By Step Instructions 2" /></div></li><div class='code-block code-block-6' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'>
